SSH to AWS Terminal Page

update the GNU wget package - it is a free GNU command line utility used to download files from the internet HTTP, HTTPS, FTP
	yum install wget

Change to root user and tmp directory
	
		sudo su 
		cd /tmp

paste the download code
	
	wget -O splunk-8.2.7-2e1fca123028-Linux-x86_64.tgz "https://download.splunk.com/products/splunk/releases/8.2.7/linux/splunk-8.2.7-2e1fca123028-Linux-x86_64.tgz"

untar the file and change dir (-C) to opt dir

	tar xvzf splunk-8.2.7-2e1fca123028-Linux-x86_64.tgz -C /opt

Create a system user and add that user to a group and add the user to sudoers list

	sudo adduser splunk 

	sudo usermod -aG sudo splunk 

create a file name user-see.conf and echo(print) the username and password into it.

	sudo echo -e "[user_info]\nUSERNAME = admin\nPASSWORD = Micah0720" > /opt/splunk/etc/system/local/user-seed.conf

When you touch a file, you're "putting fresh fingerprints on it", updating its last-modified date (or creating it if it did not yet exist)

	sudo touch /opt/splunk/etc/.ui_login

Creat Environment Variable

	echo "export SPLUNK_HOME=/opt/splunk" > /etc/profile.d/splunk.sh
	
	export SPLUNK_HOME=/opt/splunk


Change file owner and group to make sure that every file is owned by splunk

	chown -Rf splunk:splunk $SPLUNK_HOME

Enable bootstart  and Accept Licence

	sudo /opt/splunk/bin/splunk enable boot-start -user splunk --accept-license --answer-yes --no-prompt

	sudo -u splunk echo -e "[settings]\nstartwebserver = True\nenableSplunkWebSSL = True\nsslVersions = tls1.2\n" >> /opt/splunk/etc/system/local/web.conf

	sudo echo -e "DefaultLimitNOFILE=65535" >> /etc/systemd/system.conf

	sudo echo -e "DefaultLimitNOFILE=65535" >> /etc/systemd/user.conf

	echo never > /sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage/enabled

	echo never > /sys/kernel/mm/transparent_hugepage/defrag

	chown -R splunk:splunk $SPLUNK_HOME

	sudo su - splunk

	/opt/splunk/bin/splunk start


./splunk set servername Indexer-1S

./splunk set default-hostname Indexer-1

servername is used to identify the Splunk instance for features such as distributed search and defaults to <hostname>-<user running splunk>. You set this in server.conf.

default-hostname is used as default "host" field on all events coming from that Splunk instance. You set this in inputs.conf.

https://splunkonbigdata.com/how-to-uninstall-splunk-from-linux/


view linux users 
cut -d: -f1 /etc/passwd

splunk version 9
